	   <tr><td colspan=2>Depends entirely on the weapon. Many Knights disregard one-handers because generally better damaging one-handed weapons have higher delays which makes the weapon not worth it because of the lack of DPS. Damage Bonus becomes a vital variable to your total DPS and having a one-hander with two-handed speed is a big no-no. That said, this sword is pretty good because of the low delay, and excellent ratio. About the only reason I could think of people not wanting to use this over a two-hander is its lack of a good proc.<br>&nbsp;<br>**********************************<br>"<span style='color: red;'>Man who goes to bed with itchy bum, wakes with smelly fingers.</span style='color: red;'>"</td></tr>
