	   <tr><td colspan=2>Magic damage on a weapon works like this. Every time you score a hit, the creature does a save versus magic. If the creature successfully saves, the weapon does its normal range of damage. If the creature fails the save, the weapon does additional damage; in this case, it would hit as though it were a 28/25 weapon.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
